Akenerji, Eregli Demir Celik: Turkey Equity Market Preview

-- B y   A y d a n   E k s i n
-- 
2011-03-01T07:39:41Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-01/akenerji-eregli-demir-celik-turkey-equity-market-preview.html
The following stocks may be active
in  Turkey . Symbols are in parentheses and prices are from the
last close.  Turkey’s benchmark  ISE National 100 index  fell 83.47, or
0.1 percent, to 61,283.87 yesterday.    Akenerji Elektrik Uretim AS  (AKENR TI): The Turkish power
generator owned by Czech CEZ AS and Akkok group reported a loss
of 26.4 million liras ($16.5 million) last year, after a profit
in 2009, according to a statement to the  Istanbul Stock Exchange 
after the market closed yesterday. The loss exceeded an average
estimate of 18 million liras in a Bloomberg survey of 16
analysts. Akenerji rose 5 kurus, or 1.8 percent, to 2.85 liras.  Eregli Demir & Celik Fabrikalari TAS (EREGL TI): Turkey’s
biggest flat steelmaker sold its 25 percent stake in
ArcelorMittal Ambalaj Celigi Sanayi & Ticaret AS for $10.5
million to ArcelorMittal France SA, it said in a filing with the
bourse after the close yesterday. The sale was in line with the
Turkish antitrust regulator’s decision ordering the company to
divest certain stakes, it said. Erdemir, as the company is
known, fell 1 kurus, or 0.2 percent, to 4.94 liras.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Aydan Eksin in Istanbul at 
 aeksin@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
